{
  "stem": "11723.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they moved up to Budapest from Nyirbator.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They had to sell their home and whatever they owned.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And up in Budapest, he became a mashgiach, which is, to explain it to those who don't know what it is, it's a person whose responsibility is to check in places where they prepare food that the foods are prepared according to the laws of kashrut, meaning that the food is kosher.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So that's what my grandfather did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And that did not suffice for all the children and for a big household.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So they were rather poor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My mother had no dowry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I only know my mother's side of the story, so this may or may not be exactly what happened.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But when my grandmother on my father's side found out that my mother-- my mother was going to be my father's bride, she was very upset, because my father was a very eligible bachelor, and they were hoping to make a really good match for him so that maybe two family businesses will become even more successful than they were.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And-- however, my father was so much in love with my mother that he didn't budge.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And the marriage, of course, took place.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "They got married August 20, 1939, just before the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, they were supposed to go on their honeymoon to Italy, and they had to cancel it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "So my mother never got to go outside of the country, because, as I said, she wasn't a well-to-do girl, and she didn't travel.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "While my father-- [COUGHS] excuse me-- my father has traveled to Italy and to Austria, or wherever he went skiing, and also to bring in orders from England or Italy, wherever they were importing stuff from.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Textiles, that is.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
